HEADWORD: Lepidolite
<hw>Le*pid"o*lite</hw> <pr>(l⟦esl⟧*p⟦icr⟧d"⟦osl⟧*l⟦imac⟧t; 277)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>lepi`s</grk> <grk>-i`dos</grk>, a scale +
<ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>l⟦eacute⟧pidolithe</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A species of mica, of a lilac or rose-violet
color, containing lithia. It usually occurs in masses consisting of
small scales. See <er>Mica</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lepidomelane</ent>⟦br⟧
